    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `set cmdheight=0`, the message window type changes to `box`, but setting `cmdheight` back to `1` does not restore message window type.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. minimal.lua:\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._extui\").enable({\n\tmsg = {\n\t\tpos = \"cmd\",\n\t},\n})\n```\n\n2. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n3. `:lua print(\"emm\")`\n4. `set cmdheight=0`\n5. `:lua print(\"emm\")`\n6. `set cmdheight=1`\n7. `:lua print(\"emm\")`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nrestore message window type to `cmd`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-334+g3121e02ae0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.14.4-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
